We synthesized TPHP(LiClO4) polymer electrolyte by a simple “complexation and in-situ polymerization” process (Fig. 1a, b and Supplementary Fig. 1). Siloxane monomer was first synthesized by the ester substitution reaction of citric acid (CA) and tetraethyl-orthosilicate (TEOS)30 and then complexed with LiClO4. TPHP(LiClO4) polymer electrolyte was finally formed by in-situ polymerization of siloxane monomer with ethylene glycol, followed by thermal annealing in vacuum to remove the solvents. In the above acidic reaction environment, some ClO4− was reduced to low valence ClO3− by redox reaction31,32 C2H5OH + 2ClO4−→H+\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
